HEADWORD: Foreganger
<hw>Fore"gang`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prop., a goer
before cf. G. <ets>voreg⟦aum⟧nger</ets>. See <er>Fore</er>, and
<er>Gang</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A short rope grafted on a
